# Engine Contracts

## Purpose

Define all shared behavioral types in `src/core/`. Engines consume these contracts; they never redefine shapes locally. Semantic behavior for each type lives in engine-specific rules.

## Non-Negotiable Constraints

- **Single definition** — Each canonical type exists exactly once under `src/core/`. No duplicate `type Task` in `/engine/`, `/ui/`, or `/lib/`.
- **Import direction** — `engine → core` only. Core never imports from engine, ui, or orchestration.
- **Primitives** (`src/core/primitives.ts`): `Scalar` (0–100), `Timestamp`, `TrendDirection`, `RiskLevel`, `ConfidenceBand`.
- **State types** (`src/core/state/`): `UserState`, `UserMode`, `UserTrajectory`, `RecoveryDebtModel`, `CognitiveStrainModel`, `ExecutionStabilityModel`, `EmotionalFrictionModel`, `StateTransition`.
- **Task types** (`src/core/tasks/`): `Task`, `TaskCategory`, `StateCompatibility`, `CompatibilityBand`, `TimeHorizon`.
- **TaskScore family** (`src/core/tasks/`): `ExecutionWeight`, `ResistanceWeight`, `RecoveryBurden`.
- **Intervention types** (`src/core/interventions/`): `Intervention`, `InterventionLevel`, `InterventionType`, `InterventionTrigger`, `BehavioralSignal`, `SuppressionRule`, `CooldownPolicy`.
- **Adaptation types** (`src/core/adaptation/`): `AdaptationOutput`, `EnvironmentalAdaptation`, `ExecutionAdaptation`, `GuidanceAdaptation`, `PacingRecommendation`, `MessagingTone`.
- **Daily I/O** (`src/core/flow/`): `DailyInputs`, `MorningCalibrationOutput`, `MiddayRegulationOutput`, `EveningReflectionOutput`.
- **Pipeline types** (`src/core/pipeline/`): `BehavioralPipeline`, `SequencingDecision`, `ReentryProtocol`, `BehavioralInsight`.

### Key Enum Values (frozen)

- `UserMode`: RECOVERY | STABILIZING | FOCUSED | EXPANDING
- `UserTrajectory`: EXPANDING | STABLE | FRAGILE | CONTRACTING
- `InterventionLevel`: 0 (silent) | 1 (soft) | 2 (active) | 3 (structural)
- `TaskCategory`: MAINTENANCE | RECOVERY | GROWTH | ADVANCEMENT | SUPPORT
- `BehavioralSignal`: RISING_FRAGMENTATION | DECLINING_EXECUTION_QUALITY | RECOVERY_COLLAPSE | AVOIDANCE_CLUSTERING | MEANINGFULNESS_DEFERRAL | OVERCOMMITMENT_EXPANSION | DEEP_WORK_DEGRADATION | VOLATILITY_ACCELERATION | PLANNING_ESCAPE | PACING_INSTABILITY

## Implementation Guidance

- Organize by domain subdirectory matching engine ownership: `core/state/`, `core/tasks/`, `core/interventions/`, `core/adaptation/`, `core/flow/`, `core/pipeline/`.
- Export via barrel files (`index.ts`) per subdirectory.
- Types are interfaces and type aliases only — no computation, no side effects, no framework imports.
- When extending a contract, update `src/core/` first; then update engine behavior rules if semantics change.

```typescript
// src/core/tasks/task.ts — canonical definition
export type Task = {
  id: string
  title: string
  category: TaskCategory
  meaningfulness: Scalar
  cognitiveLoad: Scalar
  emotionalResistance: Scalar
  // ... remaining fields per docs/engine-contracts.md
}

// src/engine/tasks/scoring.ts — imports, never redefines
import type { Task, ExecutionWeight } from '@/core/tasks'
```

## Anti-Patterns

```typescript
// ❌ Engine-local duplicate
// src/engine/tasks/types.ts
type Task = { id: string; title: string }

// ❌ UI-extended behavioral type
// src/components/TaskCard.tsx
interface TaskWithScore extends Task { burnoutRisk: number }

// ✅ Single source
import type { Task } from '@/core/tasks'
```

## Never Do This

- Redefine `UserState`, `Task`, `Intervention`, or `AdaptationOutput` outside `src/core/`
- Add behavioral fields to types without architectural review
- Invent new behavioral constructs (focus score, discipline index) not in canonical contracts
- Put computation or scoring logic in `src/core/`
- Mirror enums with string literals scattered across engines
